Use warm plain prose in past tense. Continue directly without reopening the setting or retelling anything. Every paragraph must add a new action, discovery, feeling, or decision. Use only the named cast and place. This is narration, not a conversation: at most two short quoted lines, never back-to-back. Avoid repeated smiles, praise, names, sentence openings, and tiny-sentence chains. Do not perform any action that the required events say is merely chosen. End on a complete hook, except the final act, which ends calm and complete.

