Use short past-tense narration blocks separated by dialogue blocks. Every spoken block must begin with exactly [Glimsi] or one of the two supporting names from the contract, followed by one short spoken sentence. Never use [Name] as a noun, never add a colon after a bracket tag, and never put quotation marks in narration. Use only the named cast and place. Continue directly without reopening or retelling. Each line must cause a new action, discovery, feeling, or decision; avoid cheering, praise loops, repeated smiles, and rapid-fire reactions. Do not perform an action that the required events say is merely chosen. End on a complete hook, except the final act, which closes with quiet narration.

